\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. H. parlatorei} (J. Woods) Pilger, {\i Feddes Repert.}{\b  45}: 7 (1938) ({\i Avena parlatorei} J. Woods). Rhizome sometimes shortly creeping and with short stolons. Stem 40-80(-100) cm. Leaves 20-40(-60) cm × 2-4 mm when flat, or 1-1·3 mm in diameter when convolute, persistent when dead; ligule 3-6 mm, oblong, acute, lacerate later, glabrous. Panicle (8-)10-13(-15) cm, rather lax, with 15-45 spikelets; main axis scabridulous; primary branches with 3-5(-8) spikelets. Spikelets (8-)10-11(-12) mm, with 2-3 fertile florets. Rhachilla disarticulating only above the glumes; segments 2-3 mm, with hairs 2-3 mm; callus-hairs 1·5-2 mm; pedicel of sterile floret 3-4 mm, glabrous. Lower glume 7-10 mm, the upper 9-12 mm. Lemma 7-10(-11 ) mm, 2-fid. Palea 7-9 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Rocky slopes and screes; calcicole. • S.W. & E. Alps.} Au Ga Ge It Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  The above description refers to diploid plants. Tetraploid plants (2n = 28), known only from one locality in N.W. Italy, have spikelets (12-)14-15(-16) mm; their status needs further investigation.
