\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. H. sempervirens} (Vill.) Pilger,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  45}: 7 (1938) ({\i Avena sempervirens} Vill.). Non-flowering shoots intravaginal. Stems (30-)40-100(-150) cm. Basal leaves 15-60 cm × 0·9-1·5 mm, rigid, convolute, or flat and 2-4 mm wide, glaucous, sometimes pruinose, scabridulous, soon deciduous when dead; sheaths of basal leaves tough, long-persistent; ligule 0·5-1·5 mm, truncate, ciliate. Panicle 8-20 cm, with 30-55 spikelets; primary branches scabrid, with 3-7(-10) spikelets. Spikelets 10-14 mm, with 2(-3) fertile florets, the upper unawned. Rhachilla disarticulating only above the glumes; segments 2·5-4 mm, with hairs 4-5 mm; callus-hairs 3-4 mm; pedicel of the sterile floret 4-6 mm, sparsely hairy to glabrous. Lower glume 7-10 mm, the upper 10-12 mm. Lemma(8-)9-12 mm. Palea 8-9 mm. 2n = 42+0-5B.{\i  Rocks and stony pastures; calcicole. • S.W. Alps.} Ga It.
\par

